article.headline: Northwestern St. 85, LSU-Shreveport 64
article.story: NATCHITOCHES, La. -- Devin White scored 21 points and grabbed 12 rebounds to lead Northwestern State to a 85-64 win over LSU-Shreveport on Saturday night. William Mosley finished with 16 points and 18 rebounds for the Demons (5-4). Mosley and White each blocked four shots. Tyrone Hamilton led the Pilots (5-5) with 13 points and seven assists. Derrick Parker chipped in with 12 points and 12 rebounds. Northwestern State scored 31 points off of the Pilots' 20 turnovers. They also outrebounded LSU-Shreveport 54-42. The Pilots struggled to score, shooting 33.3 percent from the field (22-for-66) and only 14.3 percent from 3-point range (3-for-21).
